      "text": "All three deliverables are ready. Here's a summary of what was produced:\n\n### Deliverables\n\n**1. `report.md`** — A ~2,800-word research report covering:\n- **Abstract** with keywords\n- **Technology evolution** from concatenative/parametric → neural → modern deep learning\n- **Cutting-edge architectures** — detailed analysis of 7 paradigms: non-autoregressive (FastSpeech 2), end-to-end (VITS), diffusion (Diff-TTS, Grad-TTS, ProDiff), flow (Glow-TTS, Flowtron), codec LMs (VALL-E, VALL-E 2, NaturalSpeech 2), cross-lingual (VALL-E X, YourTTS), controllable (SC VALL-E, ControlSpeech), and hybrid (SimpleSpeech 2)\n- **Key challenges** — speed vs. quality, expressiveness, cross-lingual generalization, data efficiency, robustness/safety\n- **Evaluation frameworks** — subjective (MOS, CMOS, SMOS) and objective (MCD, WER, SECS, RTF) metrics, plus emerging learned metrics\n- **Practical applications** — assistants, audiobooks, accessibility, entertainment, healthcare\n- **Future directions** — RLHF for speech, Schrödinger bridges, multimodal unification, low-resource languages\n- **18 references** (all 2020–2025, IEEE format)\n\n**2. `data_analysis.csv`** — Structured data for 18 models/systems with columns: Category, Model, Year, Architecture_Type, Key_Innovation, Zero_Shot, End_to_End, Real_Time_Factor, Training_Data_Hours, MOS_Score, Speed_Category, Quality_Category\n\n**3. `visualization.png`** — A 4-panel figure showing:\n- Top-left: MOS quality scores ranked by model (with human parity line)\n- Top-right: Quality evolution over time (bubble size ∝ training data)\n- Bottom-left: Inference speed (RTF) comparison across models\n- Bottom-right: Architecture paradigm distribution by year (stacked bar)",
